@DocumentConfig[parameter_1; parameter_2]

This is some plain text. It will be @I{formatted} according to the default formatting defined in the
@B{DocumentConfig}. I want to make sure that my figure is on the same page as @Marker[id="here"]{this} block of text.

@Figure[name="my-figure"]{
    @Restrict[arrange=samepage & below; marker="here"]
    @Embed[source="figure.png"]
    This is the caption.
}

@LineBreak // one line height spacing

@PageBreak // move content after this onto the following page

@Format[columns=2, prefer=equal]{
    This paragraph will be split into two columns.
    @Embed[source="figure2.png"] // this will be embedded without a figure tag
    @Code[highlighter=c++]{ // custom highlighters can be defined within the document (or within the environment??)
        #include <iostream>
        int main()
        {
            std::cout << "Hello, World!" << std::endl;
            return 0;
        }
    }
}

// blocks like bold, italic, figure, code, can be shortened to @B, @I, @F, @C, etc...